"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/L2ZWnXMaEv3MW80pX5PQZQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m preaching to the choir here, but these sponge cakes really are some of the fluffiest, moistest sponge cakes I&#39;ve had in Chinatown. <br><br>I checked out New Kam Hing since I had 20 minutes to kill before returning to jury duty. The shop is a little hole-in-the-wall north of Canal street. When I walked in, I was surprised to see the lack of sponge cakes in the front display. Where were all the delicious cakes people kept raving about?? <br><br>Then I looked up and towards the back. HELLO plastic storage boxes stacked upon storage boxes of freshly made sponge cake! I tried one of each flavor - original, green tea, and chocolate. The cakes were lightly sweetened and you got the essence of green tea without too much bitterness. The chocolate cake had tiny bits of chocolate chip baked in - yum.<br><br>I also ordered their Vietnamese Iced Coffee for $2.50 since I figured a little caffeine kick to get through the afternoon wasn&#39;t such a bad idea. The girl behind the counter warned me that the drink would be super strong, but the strong coffee was nicely balanced out by the gallons (I exaggerate, but you get the point) of condensed milk mixed into the coffee. Did it wake me up? Sadly caffeine never has that extreme of an effect on me, but I did have a nice drink to sip on as I walked back to the courthouse.",
