"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OHxQMmZnJ8HE7VzNfYMFFw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I had been dreaming about trying this falafel so I couldn&#39;t wait for lunch time to come around.  To my chagrin I had to wait in a 25 person line.  But it moved pretty quickly and within about 15 min I was placing my order.  <br><br>Here&#39;s the lowdown:<br>-Falafel Sandwich (green falafel + hummus + Israeli salad + green cabbage + tahini sauce + everything (S&#39;rug traditional Yemeni hot sauce with cilantro, chili, garlic and olive oil, amba picked mango chutney &amp; pickles Israeli style): maybe I was just hungry out of my mind but this falafel was one of the best I have ever had.  The whole wheat pita was so soft and yummy and held the falafel sandwich together very well AND never got soggy.  The falafel was so fresh and was the right type of spicy.  The sauces are at the very top and as you keep going through the falafel sandwich you leave most of the sauces and head into the hummus portion which is not as creamy as most--which I loved.  It mixed so well and didn&#39;t overpower anything.  The sandwich was also extremely filling.  <br><br>-Date-Lime-Banana Smoothie (3 Dates, 1 Banana,  1/2 cup soy milk and 1 freshly squeezed lime): Just like everyone said, it tasted just like a banana smoothie.  But in my experience with smoothies that have bananas in them, they all taste like that.  I did like the chunks of dates that would come up through my straw from time to time but it wasn&#39;t something I&#39;d ever order again.<br><br>FINAL VERDICT: I&#39;ll be looking out for this truck more often as the wait is worth it :)",
