"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Kyo Ya is Japanese fine dining at its very best. With its location blending into the heart of the East Village, the feel of exclusivity and self-importance upon arrival will permeate the senses. The (almost entirely) wooden interior offers a feeling of tranquility and simply clears out any type of sensory overload that you might come in with in the first place.  What is left is simply the delightful service, amazing food, and the person(s) you are here to enjoy a meal with. Do yourself a favor, and just silence that cellphone for a meal that you would want to appreciate.<br><br>While I have only been able to dine here à la carte, the experience is no less grand. It is a sophisticated menu which Japanese food aficionados salivate for.  Whether it is flavor, texture, or presentation, you can just taste the efforts that go into each plate. Personal favorites include Ebi Shinjo, Chawanmushi, Kani Goma Tofu Gratin, and the Seasonal Kamadaki Rice which takes 45 minutes to prepare. And those are only cooked dishes. The  Kaiseki menu is the crown jewel experience that ranks as a can&#39;t miss and needs to be booked one day in advance.<br><br>Kyo Ya is an experience that is truth worth your time, attention, and every penny spent.",
