"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Yes, yes, and yes.  <br><br>First off, BYO in NYC.  Awesome :)  Second, the price range is extremely reasonable and the cuisine is unique.  Last, our servers were really friendly and knowledgable about the menu. <br><br>Next, let&#39;s talk about the food.  Six of us came here, so we got to try a little of everything on the menu.  The escargot are out of this world - the curry flavor added so much richness to the dish.  Loved them because they are not the typical garlic with butter and parsley flavor profile. <br>I ordered the lamb &#34;osso bucco&#34; special with pureed carrots and I could eat that the rest of my life if I had the chance.  <br><br>The pamplemousse salad is good and refreshing and prepares your palate for an assault of rich flavor.  The stuffed avocado was tasty as well.  The burgers were all good and it&#39;s nice that you can dress them how you want.  The jerk chicken is good ( I still liked my lamb better!!) and the soufflé - you rarely see soufflé on menus anymore and they know what they&#39;re doing here. <br><br>I wish I lived in Brooklyn so I could eat here all the time!",
