"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/9Lq02-rtpaTJh_gnGfoSJw/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Absolutely wonderful sushi and the BYOB make this place a great casual and reasonably priced option! My friend picked up a few big cans of Sapporo from the corner store nearby and we headed to the restaurant for the first seating of the night. <br><br>The place is tiny with just about 12 seats and it almost feels like you are sitting in someone&#39;s home. We were assigned seats by the door at the corner of the sushi bar (the only type of seating they have, no individual tables) and at first we were a bit disappointed to be so close to the door since it was freezing out. We then realized that it was prime seating since we were both able to watch the sushi chefs work and since there are just three seatings, there really is no foot traffic coming in and out during the meal. Score!<br><br>There were ice bins at each of our stations and we were able to keep our Sapporo on ice and refill our glasses at our leisure. We also received water as well to cleanse our palates at each bite. <br><br>We started with the uni sampler and the scallop and both were amazing. The uni from California is way better than the Japanese one, but it was great to try a side by side comparison. The scallop was super fresh and a nice sized portion as well. <br><br>We then got the Omakase and I love how the sushi rice is served just over room temperature. There was a buttery richness to many of the pieces and my favorites were the ones served at the beginning of the meal. (That might be because I was getting fuller and fuller as the meal progressed.)<br><br>To end the meal we got the most perfect bowl of miso soup. It was a wonderful meal and I definitely left satisfied. I will be sure to come back if I can snag another reservation for sure! My new favorite place (tied with Sasabune) for Omakase in the city!",
