"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"My mom used to buy the panelle sandwich on her way to school back in the 1920&#39;s. , this place has been here when a panelle and a rice ball was sniffed at by the same types that swarm this neighborhood now.<br><br>I laugh when I see the clueless yuppie types not knowing what to order and defaulting to drink wine with everything Italian. Though I notice yuppies are big drinkers, they couldn&#39;t handle a cold manhattan special. It&#39;s got to have alcohol in it for them. They seem so stressed out all the time...<br><br>This and sams pizza on court and the wonderful ladies next door in the &#34;candy store&#34; are what&#39;s left of my real Brooklyn. Not the faux overpriced snobby one hoisted on us now.<br><br>Go next door and ask about Armando who lived on president street, or the restaurant on Colombia and president that  Marilyn Monroe went to. Google crazy joe gallo he hung out right around the corner. <br><br>The start of the entire cosa Nostra started on Colombia street. ...it&#39;s was a real neighborhood. The faux wanna be manhattan one now of 2013 doesn&#39;t do it justice.",
