"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/bdfs230yEFi0g9fgdCT-7g/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"So first off: BIG shout out to Louis and I always forget the young lady (business owner&#39;s name) but to her as well... they ALWAYS take care of me...<br><br>So I walked in on a limb last year and Louis was the first person that greeted me. He gave me the rundown of each flavor of Gelato they were serving. He was very patient and very nice about giving out samples (6 of them at a time). They have a ridiculous amount of flavors to choose from (there&#39;s something for everyone, I promise). Their menu, I THINK, is pretty extensive for a cafe and it&#39;s reasonably priced. They decor inside is very chic and stylish. Great colors. I particularly enjoy their lounge area in the back with the French doors. <br><br>The location of the Cafe is something that I appreciate. It&#39;s only 7 minutes from my house. Parking is pretty good provided you get there at a decent time (still figuring that out). I go there to study every Sunday and can usually find parking in front of the Cafe. I&#39;ll be a regular there as much as I can. So my favs so far:<br><br>Gelato: Definitely the berries w/ lavender. It&#39;s very floral and clean tasting.<br>Food: Their meatballs with pasta was pretty good for a Cafe. I was expecting less than par but the meatballs were a nice size and seasoned well. <br>Drink: I love their raspberry white hot chocolate. So bad for you, but SOO good. <br><br>I can&#39;t wait to see what Louis and the crew have in store this summer. So CHEERS to your first year. I&#39;m so happy for you guys. Congratulations are in order... <br><br>-Alvin",
