"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Oh, Brooklyn Bagel, we love you. and by &#34;we&#34; I mean, Astoria. <br><br>New York City Bagels are iconic... and it&#39;s because of places like Brooklyn Bagel, bottom line. This place is always packed with good reason(s): the superb quality of the bagels, freshness of the MULTIPLE cream cheeses, piping hot coffee, speedy precise service, the several convenient locations... the list goes on and on. <br><br>However, here is what kicks this place up a notch (as if what I just listed wasn&#39;t all you&#39;d want from a bagel shop). Each week they have a &#34;cream cheese flavor of the week&#34; and they really let their imaginations run wild. I think I saw a red velvet flavor, a nutella flavor... I mean come on. It&#39;s like they know me.<br><br>Then, let&#39;s take this a bit farther why don&#39;t we. They have SPELT bagels for a healthier option, did they read my mind? No, they just know what people care about in their neighborhood. They also have tofu cream cheese that also come in unique flavors. <br><br>Just yesterday, I had a spelt bagel with tofu cinnamon, walnut, raisin cream cheese. It was decadent and delicious, without all the guilt of me scarfing down a regular bagel. Thanks, guys. You make me so happy.<br><br>Also, the coffee (however you like it) will impress. And that&#39;s all you really want to wash that bagel down with, right? Well even if you don&#39;t... they have a great juice selection including freshly squeezed orange. Awesome!<br><br>Breakfast sandwiches are also a popular option here. My husband&#39;s favorite is the bacon, egg, and cheese on a croissant. And why wouldn&#39;t it be... it&#39;s bacon, eggs, and cheese on a CROISSANT.<br><br>A++ for Brooklyn Bagel.",
