"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Degustation?  it was &#34;De-gu-sting.&#34;  &#34;Degustingly&#34; awesome that is.  Me Gusta De-gusta. Hurray!   GF surprised me on a &#34;date night&#34; here, and wow, perfect place for a date.  And with that, I emphasize that this place is no bueno for large groups.  There&#39;s only about 20 seats (think sushi-bar style) so unless you want to be awkwardly talking to your friends in an &#34;L&#34; shape, avoid it.  Instead, take that special someone who appreciates the meticulous details and presentation of small bites done Spanish style, all while watching the chefs prepare and create the dishes in front of your eyes.  I dare you not to smile when you watch the chefs torch and caramelize those lovely Torrejas (french toast but I call it more of a bread pudding).<br><br>We didn&#39;t opt for the tasting menu (realized that it featured the same items from the menu a-la-carte (and there isn&#39;t that many anyways). Ask the friendly staffs for recommendation; they make you feel welcome.<br><br>The menu changes seasonally so it wouldn&#39;t make sense to pinpoint a particular dish.  However, I can point out that each vegetable/ meat dish was cooked perfectly, seasoned well, yet still retained its natural flavor.   My favorite was the fascination of seeing so many different ingredients complimenting and enhancing a dish.  What the dishes lacked in portion, it made up for it in quality (and presentation).  Quality over quantity, my friends and in life, you pay for what you get: a kick ass meal.",
