"reviewcomment":"I&#39;m no ramen connoisseur, but I can tell you the hour-long line is worth the wait. This place puts the (hoo)RA! in ramen!<br><br>My sister and I showed up mid-afternoon, probably 3 o&#39;clock, and we still had to wait 40 minutes for a table. The hostess took my number, and we stepped outside to walk around while we waited.<br><br>Once you&#39;re called in for your table, the hostess walks you down a hallway toward he dining room, and upon announcing your arrival to the dining room and kitchen staff, everyone greets you in Japanese.<br><br>If you&#39;re a small party, or even a moderate sized one, you&#39;ll likely be seated with other folks. You basically take a seat where ever they put you, and get off your high horse if you think this is weird, because this place won&#39;t be changing its customs any time soon.<br><br>I ordered the classic ramen and my sister ordered to Umami. Both were incredible. The broth stuck to the noodles and the dishes weren&#39;t salty at all. The noodles were fresh, as were the rest of the ingredients, and the service was fast! Which is impressive considering how long the wait was to get in.<br><br>One of the best parts is the glass looking into he kitchen. The chefs all seem to really be enjoying themselves and it&#39;s fun seeing them create each dish. <br><br>My only regret was not ordering the rolls everyone seemed to have that looked like weird Japanese tacos. Next time, they&#39;re mine.",
