"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve passed this place a number of times before, and never thought to step foot inside until a good friend suggested we stop here to catch up. It was a good suggestion, and it&#39;s become a bit of a regular spot ever since.<br><br>It&#39;s a very cozy location, and my experience with whoever is behind the counter has always been pleasant. What&#39;s really worth the repeat visits is the food, of course. The chai I had there was aromatic and delicious, and the menu selections are good enough that my friend and I can order different items just to mix &amp; match. I&#39;m particularly fond of the smoked turkey and pesto panini, as well as the prosciutto and mozzarella variety. It&#39;s nice to be able to get a panini from someplace that hasn&#39;t had the thing sitting in a refrigerator for hours waiting to be reheated.<br><br>If you happen to come in when they have the tomato soup with sour cream, do yourself a favor and have it. On a cold winter day (and we&#39;ve had a lot of those lately), it really hits the spot. Ditto for their chocolate brownie. <br><br>I really enjoy the cafe atmosphere. That is, you go and order your food, and they pretty much leave you to your own devices until you&#39;re ready to go. You can have a nice, leisurely meal or snack and not worry about how long you&#39;ve been there. <br><br>I&#39;m sure I&#39;ll be out here several more times before winter is out. Maybe I&#39;ll see you there?",
