"reviewcomment":"This is the ideal restaurant for an intimate, speak-easy dining experience for lovers of Japanese cuisine. Part of the allure definitely lies in the level of secrecy that comes with Bohemian. Then once you get past the private reservation line, the experience will most likely live up to expectations. The ambiance and exclusivity is fantastic, and the small space only enhances that vibe. The menu is truly special.<br><br>The tasting menu is ideal for first-time goers to get a sense of what they like and what they will want each time they visit subsequently.  Personal highlights are the pan-roasted branzino, uni croquette, mac-n-cheese, and foie gras soba.  You can&#39;t really go wrong with anything on the menu, and fans of washu beef will leave Bohemian very happy.<br><br>Bohemian is an experience very similar to that of Sakagura, maybe just a bit more intimate. It is simply the perfect place for celebrating any occassion.",
