"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Sublime.<br><br>If there is just one word I can use to describe the experience at Sushi Yasuda, it is the word &#39;sublime.&#39; Everything here is amazing, well thought out, and executed to perfection. Came here on a Wednesday night with a reservation, was promptly seated on the dot at 7:30. Upon sitting down, I stared at the immaculate setup before me....plate, chopsticks, wet napkin...it all felt so zen-like and organized, like a general getting his troops ready for war. A war on delicious sushi.<br><br>Ordered the omakase...and while I was shell shocked at the price tag (around $450 for 2 people), it was worth the price. Course after course of delicious, fresh fish kept arriving in front of me, with no visible end in sight. Just when we thought we were done, more fish kept showing up. The favorites of the night were the uni, the two types of eel, the two types of mackerel, and the fatty tuna maki roll. Everything was top notch, the service excellent, and the ambiance made me feel like for a few hours, that I was actually in Japan.<br><br>Run, sprint, fly, whatever you do, don&#39;t just walk here. Find a way to get here and experience the most delicious sushi you will ever have outside of Japan!",
