"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Came here for a birthday with a few friends. Nice environment, very courteous staff. <br><br>Seared Sea Scallops - The scallops were great, not over cooked still very juicy, with the bed of avocado and sweet soy. The dish was very well compiled.<br><br>Fresh Mozzarella - It was a very nice portion that they gave us. The red wine vinegar marinated portobello mushrooms had just the right amount to not over power the dish. I felt the olive oil could of <br><br>For entree my cousin and I shared the porter house for two (cooked medium) and it was close to being cook perfectly. The cut that we had I thought was good, well portioned. Cutting thru the steak was pretty easy but not like butter.<br><br>My friends got the Ribeye and T-Bone. Both of them felt like quality of the cut of meat that they had (which I tried) wasnt as good as other steakhouses. The T-Bone was seemed like the steak was cooked and left out for pickup for a while. While the steaks rested they cooked more than it should have. The ribeye was a bit tough even tho it was cooked at medium.<br><br>For sides we shared baked potato w/ butter, cream of spinach, mash potato, and sauteed mushrooms and spinach. It seems to me a lot of steakhouses tend to fall thru in this category. I didnt care too much for the sides but if i had t pick one of the few that we got was the baked potato but that&#39;s the skill in preparing a baked potato is very minimal. The others felt that sauteed mushrooms and spinach was the best choice in this case.",
